  "text": "ROS-Intracellular reactive oxygen species were detected using the method of [CITATION_1] with dichlorofluorescein diacetate (H 2 DCF-DA; Sigma). H 2 DCF-DA was added at a final concentration of 5 mol L Ϫ1 to 3 ml of fully acclimated phytoplankton culture and incubated in the light under normal culturing conditions. Cell cultures treated similarly, but incubated in the dark, were used as controls. The assay then measured only photogenerated ROS. Cells were collected at 15,000 ϫ g for 3 min; then the supernatant was diluted fourfold and measured in a spectrofluorometer with excitation and emission wavelengths of 488 and 520 nm, respectively. Values are reported as relative fluorescent units normalized to cell number.",
